76561198018821714,Recommended,328080,32573439,Posted: 19 June,all,drewbicus,"TL;DR: Buy this game, it's amazing and fun.Long review:I bought the game as a birthday gift to myself and am incredibly pleased. It's fun, entertaining, and has more depth than you might suspect. The art style is simple and clean. Game play is simple to learn while offering great challenge.Resource management is efficient: Wood, Stone, Food, and Crystals are the basic four to be gathered from the map. They can each be refined into secondary, advanced resources.Your citizens are not directly managed other than being able to pick them up and move them around. They operate by AI based on how you manage your village development. This saves a lot of click and drag that bogs down other titles. It was a great design choice. Citizens also level up based on their work, becoming more efficient and stronger over time.Your village succeeds or fails based on your method of developing it, and defending it. Monsters will start attacking your village within a few days of starting it. The game brings in aspects of RTS games and Tower Defense as your primary combat systems. Much of your defense is managed by tower construction and building obstacles to slow the advance of attacking nasties.The game can be played in settings from Sandbox mode to Nightmare mode, meaning from ""no monsters"" to ""Do you feel lucky, punk?"" The hardest level can pose a challenge to the most advanced village-building gamer.The game is not complete, but updates are frequent. The developer is present on the Steam forums and hosts Twitch streams to keep players up to date with development. He's also very interactive with the player base and open to new ideas. This is the kind of developer who keeps improving the game and providing new content on a regular basis. Check in on his streams, you'll like the guy and his video-bombing cat.I give this game a 10/10 because it's great as is, getting better all the time, and the developer is a fantastic example of how to conduct business when creating a game."
