ndomized.Currently in:-are different basic buildings like a farm, different kinds of housing (tent and house), lighting, defensetowers, walls, structures to earn ressources-a mapeditor to create your own maps (is kinda easy, just the dev is doing some very ugly ones)-different profile without any use at the moment-a settings option menu-2 types of monsters (zombie and slime)-1 type of food-2 types of usable ressources (stone and wood)-3 types of non usable ressources at the moment (3 different crystaltypes)-a kinda good soundtrack (sounds very pixely)-a very sweet pixel look, zoomable camera (although a bit clunky in performance then)Note: you can enter a beta branch with going to properties of the game, which gives you access to a ""unstable"" version of the game with more features. I highly recommend  to do this, i experienced no crashes on the unstable compared to the basic version which crashed often and got more content from it.How to do this is described on the forum.My review is based of the Unstable Version 2 InDev12 on the Beta Branch.I can recommend this game as an early access game. Even unfinished it is very playable and has enough content to get fun out of it and be creative with the editor to get even more challenge or just experiment.I bought it for 7.49€ and i think it was worth the price. I think 15€ are a bit much for the content at the moment and if you want to wait till it gets cheaper or has more content, then wait.But i think it will definetely be worth this price tag with a bit more content or even when its finished and for an Early Access Game, it delivers more than others do.Its one of the good Early Access Games."
