,Not Recommended,328080,15811813,"Posted: 13 May, 2015",all,Ryan Dorkoski,"Edit (2/17): Review is quite outdated. A lot of dev work has happened. At this point, I have no intention of revisiting the game, but I did spend the time originally to play and review, so my review stands. Such can be a consequence of long development cycles, and releasing software early.---I *love* citybuilders and population managers. I thinkGnomoriaandBanishedare two of my most played games on Steam with about 60 and 30 hours respectively. I put about 40 hours intoDwarf Fortress, and quite enjoyed it. WhileRPCdesperately wants to be like these titles, it is very far off - in a bad way.First thing everybody should know is that there is no below-ground mining.Your world consists of a small-ish 'asteroid' that is one layer of ground thick, floating in space. There are frequent areas of the map that are just 'holes' where you can see the space behind the one-layer thick ground. I am certain that this strange mechanism is a result of limited money/resources/programming ability (idk), and was not intended.The allure of the games cited as inspiration (listed in first paragraph) was largely because you could take 'stuff' out of the ground and organize it above ground! When you take that away, I am significantly less interested.You cannot rotate buildings because it would take too much effort to redraw the images.I get it - prioritize developement, but this is something very basic that needs to be mentioned. It further hints at where this game is going. I would imagine these images could be done in a long weekend, am I right? I am not trying to be harsh, but potential buyers need to be aware of these things.These are the main two issues I have but there are a myriad of others such as map and individual person custimazation that I will not go into fully.There are also very few buildings at this point.Otherwise the music is quite good, and the artwork is pretty cool.This game probably was released on Early Accessa bit too early.I got it for half price, and am fine with it because I want to try any and all citybuilders/population managers.To my Steam friends: if you haven't playedGnomoriaorBanishedyet, go for those!If you are like me and have exhausted those, this *might* quench your thirst for a bit.I don't believe any of the issues I put forth will be resolved (I mean its one guy working on this), but if they are, I will alter my review. Thanks for reading,-Ryan"
