76561198081029277,Recommended,328080,29922293,Posted: 14 February,all,Frostie McSnowcone,"The game is very good and could be feasably released as it is. I see many people comparing it to Banished - which is a fair comparison. However, in my opinion, this game has already overtaken Banished with its mechanics. Banished was released and forgotten by its developer, has no end game and no requirement to expand unless you want to go until your village collapses in on itself (though I do like the game very much and you'll probably enjoy it if you enjoy this). This game also has no end game, but it recieves updates, tweaks and there is a rapid difficulty curve with the incoming mobs that forces you to expand.Something else I've noted in the negative reviews is that NPCs fail to pick up items on the ground - which is not true. They do not pick it up immediately, but they will do so when an NPC of the appropriate job comes along and is empty handed. NPCs also do not ""cross the village"" to attack mobs on a regular basis. Some wil break off from their job when nearby a mob or fight - potentially to fight or run. In general, there is no major issue with the AI, assuming you have everything needed for it to function. The most notable frustration is that when they are attack in the middle of a task they will drop their item to fight or run. Once they calm, they are confused and it's hit or miss as to whether they'll continue their job or start again. You may want to use your Godly powers to aid them.Pros:Nice musicFunctioning AIUpgrade systemNPC progression systemSmoothe gameplayAbility to move desirable resources to another worldGodlike abilitiesExisting difficulty curveCons:Difficulty curve is very steepLack of a variety of buildingsLack of a great variety of resources to handleEasy to get mobbed by the exponential increase in monstersCannot rotate buildingsTents take up a 3x3 space when they're more suited to 2x2 <- surprisingly frustrating to meCan take a long time to rack 