,Recommended,328080,12734023,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,Ex3cUtIoN11 **MEDIC**,"This game many fun. Is liek Mincraft but so many more features like a the game goes to nighttime after it is daytime for so long. and you have to get things like wood and stone unlike minecraft were you just punch things. this gaem is super realistic. it has features like blood and water but its not just blood. like it spreads its cool..Congratulations, you read what it would look like if a 12 year old wrote a review for this game. I will now enlighten you with my actual review. For the record, this is build 10-31-2014. Currently this game is very limited in the features. Before you ever start a game it lets you know that there is just the core game to play with a few things added. You have some maps to pick between, some of them are test maps which narrows down the ""usuable"" maps even further. When you start, you get 24 villagers and have to build your village center. To do this, you must collect wood and stone from nearby sources. Once the village center is completed you gain access to more buildings; however, this too is extremely limited. You can build storage for food, wood, and stone. There are three different sizes of houses you can build, two sizes of farms, torches for light and walls.  Walls currently serve no purpose other than to look cool and to really make that retro looking pixelated castle feel that you wanted when you bought this game.  The villagers will marry and have children which causes the need for more food and shelter. This may feel slow and boring but once you start getting around 90-100 villagers it becomes more demanding. I managed to get over 410 villagers but due to lag and food shortages, the best i could do was simply let people start dying. Despite the numerous deaths, the villagers, or vermin, were breeding out of control and continually increased in numbers until my game crashed-- it is early access after all. Currently the game simulated building a colony and watching them thrive or spew blood across the canvas as they starve to death due to your incompetence as a pathetic god figure.  Either way, this game is already fun in its current state and if what they already have announced as future plans are promises and not just ideas that are never implemented, this game will only ever get better and I anticipate its official launch.  All I ask is that saves are added so my vermin(oops, I mean, people) infested islands can be saved before the villagers feel the wrath of torment of not only being starved to death in the midst of a famine, but instead, the excruciating pain of being.... deleted."
