76561198013055491,Recommended,328080,33091240,Posted: 1 July,all,Konscience,"At the time I'm writing this:(July 2017)The game feel great, it make me want to play further (after 10ish hours of gameplay), I may complete this review later as the game devellopment progress.The graphisms are phenomenal for a retro pixel art style, every building have its own animation when raining, have several state of completion in construction as in destruction, as well as different states of use and upgrades, meaning several dozen of sprites for the same building.I do feel that quality is a big deal to the 1-man devellopment studio that is SixtyGigs Games.The gameplay is a blend of city builder/colony survival and God games, if you want references, I think the game is inspired from the first Black&White from LionHead Studio, wich is my favorite God game.My favorite part is the god powers, being able to interract with the world in real time by your own hand or via magic powers, doesn't feel broken of overpowered, but just fine as it is implemented.For the moment the ""defense"" aspect of the game is heavily reliant on the ""tower defense"" type, but next update will provide the possibility to have patrol of armed citizen, I'm really looking forward to this.The music soundtrack is great and as the devellopment progress SFX caused by gameplay element are becoming more and more complete and immersive.I don't like much making a list of pro and con, especially in a game that please me, so I'll just underline the major positive and negative point.Positive one:The gameplay doesn't feel limited, it's not the kind of game where once you build every building you feel as if you played the whole game.That's the kind of game that make you think, think about how to play more efficiently, and not necessarily in an unique fashion: you can devellop your own way of playing, and don't have to adopt ""One uber-way of doing things"" that would soon be written down in a guide, that every lazy people would then apply all along in the game.If you want examples of what I'm tring to put in word: You have a lack of food, you have several way to resolve the situation: You can either assign more workers to the farm, build a more efficient farm that need less workers, you can use your powers to make the naturals fields of whatever you're growing, or you can even gather the food yourself with your own divine hand. And thoses choices apply for everything: wood/ water/stone/crystals ressources, defense against enemies, health care etc...Negative one:I do think the ""tower defense"" aspect to be a bit limiting as way of defence and also breaking realism.Not in a very bad way tho, tower defense in this game is fun, but while your villagers can defend themselves to a certain extend against sparse monsters, after some days it's no longer a viable way at all, and you need to place towers and make a labyrinth out of walls to be able to survive (there are several level of difficulties mind you, so there may be a sweet spot between the tower-defense and the totally peacefull mode.)BUT:Next update will provide the ability to create patrols, sparring between citizen, watchtowers, and guard houses for them and their equipement, so it may become a viable way to defend your town the dwarf-fortress way (with your own citizens, trained for combat).I'm really eager to see what the next update will bring, as this game really feel promising!And, please forgive my broken engrish, I'm french, and curently trying hard to improve my english."
