76561198013474409,Recommended,328080,32211592,Posted: 5 June,all,macfire19,"Let's see... this game is hard to categorize but I think the best way to name it is a godlike village simulator.  The way the game works is you are a god and you place down a camp with villagers and help them thrive by giving them orders to build/harvest.  You must also defend your village from monsters by building towers and making a maze (maze isn't required... but it helps a ton).  I really enjoy playing this game, and the developer is great and always makes great improvements to the game while listening to feedback.  With the most recent update (as of June third, 2017) you can now change the difficulty higher, or even make your own custom difficulty, which is really neat.  The game also includes a built-in map editor to make your own maps (steam workshop support planned for the future to introduce better map sharing).  All-in-all this is a really fun game, and well worth the price tag."
