76561198002745943,Recommended,328080,32490153,Posted: 16 June,all,NF_Spasp,"Fantastic ""little"" village survival game. The developer steadily brings out updates with brand new content, with a massive ""defence"" patch (2nd June 2017), allowing upgrades of defence positions, in addition to all the other upgradeable buildings.The visuals are crisp and satisfying to look at, with everything from colors and shape of everything falling properly into place, and several varieties of every tile-set, apart from water. There is a world map where you can choose any map to visit to look at this variation; blue forests to ashen sands, and marble mountains to blackstone.After choosing a map on the world screen, you start off the game on an uninhabited map, prompting you to place your village center where you want it to be. Taking a close look at the map for a minute or two can make things much harder or easier depending on location. Shortly afterwards you start to notice the myriads of buildings at your disposal, and work you have to do in order to survive; it might be overwhelming at first, but it really is quite simple once you get going:- Select resources for collection.- Build stuff you need: Collection buildings for wood/stone etc, production, defences, refining, etc etc.- Don't die!- Repeat.You cannot control villagers directly, however. They will do the jobs that are given to them via the resources you select and the job list UI on the left side of the screen. This is somewhat a weak point, as the control you have is extremely low. I would like to have something of a flag system; where you can place flags at certain locations that works like additional orders to your villagers. Like flags for avoiding areas, prioritizing resource collection at a certain area so you don't have to reassign those orders all the time. or even attacking an area. The Avoid Area flag would be great, as villager AI is very bad when they fight monsters, often dying for no reason when they could run away into their houses to heal. The AI is the game's biggest weakness, but really is not a big issue.The gameplay is affected by several factors. Weather and seasons play a huge role. If it's windy and rainy, your villagers gets slowed down significantly. It does not rain in the winter and nothing grows, and in the summer villagers drink more water and heat up frequently. It's a lot to take into consideration. Luckily, you have several spells to use! Your spell points regenerate over time and from particles floating around the map after something has died, and can be spent to cast storms, picking things up, quickly growing nature stuff, healing and more. Be careful where you cast that fireball though!You are probably gonna fail spectacularly the first times around, unless you picked the easiest difficulties at the world screen.  Either way it's a good time, and really satisfying to build your favorite village. The game is very cheap for what you get for it, the replayability is immense, and increased by several magnitudes by the map editor and ability to share maps over the workshop. Enjoy!"
