76561197968132580,Recommended,328080,14907713,"Posted: 15 March, 2015",all,NilartPax,"Dev Review:The dev is very active on his forums.  He is always looking from new crashes to take care of (the stable release is pretty stable now. 5/15/16).  He is an indie dev making a good little game.  He is indeed the developer who listens to you.  Take a look at the discussion board and you will see he has responses on the majority of threads.As far as game development goes, there have been significant and continual changes in the last year.  Every aspect of the game has matured.  More god powers.  Monster spawns are different.  Monsters will break down walls if they can't find a way in.  There are many more tower types than before.  there are now seasons.  There is a ""full map"", which lets you take stuff from one village to help with or start another if you survive long enough to prosper. ;)Game Review:Very fun little game.  The best way I can describe it is a God/tower defense village sim.  The game is similar to Banished in some aspects, but with the outside threat of the Undead.  It shares some aspects of Majesty as well.  It is a race against time to try and stay safe while the zombies and skeletons spawn (the monster spawning is going through some big changes in the current cycles so I left this a bit vague).You don't have direct control of your guys which can lead to some hilarious situations; where someone runs from a zombie away from defense towers and deeper into trouble, or circles around a barricade to try and get that lump of stone that was dropped on the wrong side of the wall, etc.  A ""grab"" God power has been added so you can take care of some of these problems... if you are there to see it.If you like Banished and tower defense games, or just want some good liero-style blood, this game is worth picking up, especially if it's on sale.  *Read what the dev has to say about the early access game before you purchase.*Oh, and if you are looking for a god game this is so much better than Godus it's not even funny.edit: Updating review to current build - 1 year since purchase and I'm still enjoying the game.  At the games current price and my current hours.. I've paid 12 cents per hour of enjoyment. =)"
