76561198110881362,Recommended,328080,16381704,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,ash,"This is a fun base building game with zombie apocalypse overtones ;)  It's quite a challenging game, you really need to get started on building your food production and population from the first minute in order to survive for any decent time.The position of your base is also critical.   It's important to try to use natural barriers (water, rocks, forests) as protection from zombies.  You can wall yourself in, but building even wooden fences can take a decent amount of resources and time.The game/developer seems to be of the opinion that losing should be ""fun"".  In other words it's a base builder game in the sprit of roguelikes such as Dwarf Fortress.  It's far easier to just pick up and play than most roguelikes, but if you don't like that style of game you may struggle with this.Then again, if you haven't tried a similar game before, this would be a great intro.It's still in early access, so some of the building choices are a bit limited, but the developer seems to be adding features every few weeks which is great.A few suggestions:An in game legend (easily accessible), with text explaining each of the small icons (emoticons) that appear above villagers and enemies would be handy.Needs a pause option.Maybe a bit more personality for the villagers and enemies would be nice.This is a fun game and has the potential to be even better."
