 2! not even end of day but end of dawn.Villagers are smarter but still not there, as above they will walk away from the town or the farthest building into the middle of no where and just idle there... until they see a zombie and then they will rush to it, and then rush to the next and the next and the next... until they die.  Yes they will run away but that only lasts a couple steps and then they will see a zombie and run and attack, it's a game of ping pong now with the run, attack, run, attack action... the game really needs a way to contain the villagers, either walls with gates or a ""no go"" zone that you can mark villagers to not cross.Defence buildings are useless, zombies heal faster then the buildings can regenerate, spawn faster then the buildings can regenerate and it appears the more you build, the more zombies you bring.Once you mark a building to be built you can't pause it (Being worked on but the button doesn't work still), you can't lower it in the queue and you can't cancel it, you can only dismantle it, instant if nothing was delivered to the building, but if the building had even 1 item delivered to it a builder has to go to the building to dismantle it...Looking forward to the next patch but the game is still too unbalanced to be enjoyable"
