,Recommended,328080,34140003,Posted: 9 August,all,EsKa,"(edited)Ok this one deserves a full review.It's a very decent game oscillating between a colony builder and a god game.Pros:+ Complete and complex colony builder, which in itself is pretty rare.+ Lots of content, game modes and yet feels appropriately balanced+ Cute art style, it's not earth shattering but it does its job and has a certain charm to it+ Features a decent tutorial and hint system teaching you the basics, it's far from perfect of course, but it's there.+ Actively developed and regularly updatedCons+ The user interface while not being attrocious feels more like a developer debug menu than a polished thing. It's serviceable, but counter intuitive, requiring more clicks than necessary and where information isn't displayed sufficiently/efficiently.+ The ""mana"" system allowing you to spawn pretty much any resource or use powers feels like a placeholder for features / buildings / tech that have yet to be implemented.+ the whole turret / combat /military side feels a bit weak.All in all it's a very interesting game in a fairly niche genre. It's not without flaws but nothing game breaking. For that price, it's definitely recommended."
