76561198013132245,Recommended,328080,32388451,Posted: 13 June,all,huminado,"The compelling element of gameplay: increasing building technology requirements (i.e. materials) to allow a larger number of buildings.That little game mechanic drives the whole game, blocking new buildings from coming up until prerequisite buildings have been placed and required materials are available. It is implemented by requiring the city center to get upgraded, and each subsequent upgrade requires new materials that must be manufactured. Great design and I thoroughly enjoy the amount of decision-making generated by the mechanic. Each new building consumes a ""building slot"".This game is sort of a combo: tower defense and city building are the main mechanic. But the game also adds a god spell-casting mechanism, which allows casting fireballs, earthquakes, holy golems, healing aura, resurrect the ghost, and a few others, all with varying essence costs, which is slowly building up over time according to how happy villagers are.Most importantly, there is a ""grab anything"" spell that allows grabbing enemies, friends, resources -- just not buildings. You can use it to move enemies away if they are causing too much trouble, or saving your villagers before certain death, or collecting resources your villagers aren't collecting fast enough. Each time you use it it burns essence depending on how long you grab something. This has the side-effect of making game-pause disallow touching the board in any way (pause also won't let you use the building-selection menus, but the dev claims he will change this eventually). Not being able to change a paused board I find annoying, especially when it's only reason is to support a strange game-play mechanism. The game develops an arcade-like feel (i.e. frantically moving things around), when it's supposed to be a city-builder. It's odd.  [Most city builders involve dropping ""blueprints"" that workers eventually build the buidings on top of - but this is the first city builder I have seen that won't let you pause and place as many blueprints as you like - you have to unpause the game to do that.]Another odd mechanism is that the global map (where you choose the submap the village will be placed in) can have units (enemy or ally) in ""limbo"", and they can be portalled out of a map or back in as you like. I scratch my head at why this was put in - but there it is.But wait! There's more! There are also 2 other mini-games: - collect the essence and - find the friend or foe.Collect The EssenceCollect the essence involves moving your mouse around essence that results from enemy deaths or other triggers that have it free-floating in the atmosphere. The way the essence follows bezier curves is fun to watch and it's a bit relaxing break from the rest of the game.Find The Friend Or FoeThe other minigame ""find the friend or foe"" involves hovering the mouse close enough to ground units to see whether they are enemies or friends (your own villagers or nomads). If you don't have your mouse close enough, you can't see what they are. This I think was a really bad UI choice for the sake of creating a mini-game. I find it purely annoying. Your mileage may vary.ConclusionThe game involves several mini-games, some add and some detract from the core gameplay, which is castle (or city) building. Because this is still early access, who knows? But I feel I've already gotten my money's worth purely for the mechanisms I like, and it's very easy to keep playing this until the late hours of the night. For that reason alone, it's worth a buy."
,Recommended,328080,34719010,Posted: 3 September,all,ChillyThePengu1n,This game is awesome!. Think of Minecraft and Simcity or something like that. Totally worth it!
76561198070352043,Recommended,328080,33476396,Posted: 12 July,all,ColdOneK,"This is a review for InDev 26 -- 7/12/17This review acknowledges that this game is currently in early access -- and being actively developedThis game is currently quite enjoyable w/ it's lite village management ++ tower defense design.Very similar to games like dwarf fortress and gnomoria w/ far less of the tedium involved w/ micromanaging every little thing. You'll also have your defenses tested nightly - rather than randomly - a bonus for unlucky DF players who would go in-game years w/out a siegeA lot of the mechanics are unfinished - and balance isn't there yet - of courseBut overall - I'm very hopefull for what's to come.-- Boss monsters - and the blood moons-- Villagers leveling up may actually give us heroes in the future that go hunt down items/etc-- Reasons to try to expand your walls-- More village management w/ a reason to play in the different biomes-- Fire elementals - that actually take damage in water or while it's raining. ;]A few annoying things/complaints here and there---- Majority of enemies in the game are resistant 40%+ to piercing damage - making it pointless to build bow towers or ballistae irregardless of what the ""helpful"" hint says-- No AOE towers - there is a static tower - that is useless by the time you get the resources to build it because of its hilariously low damage and lack of damage upgrades-- Spectres - immune to crush + pierce - forces magic damg w/ absurd health numbers-- road upgrades are tedious - should happen automatically as the waymakers collect resources-- no house upgrades - would think you could upgrade between the three choices as time progressed-- cannot cancel when something is tagged for dismantling -- why?-- storm + earthquake power - despite incredibly high costs are useless as damaging spells - storm's is only effective as a utility to force rain - and earthquake has basically no purpose-- resources that really shouldn't - tend to disappear over time - when not placed in storage -- such as iron ore - logs - or rocks --- despite the lack of controls like ""gather X resource until I have X number - otherwise do nothing""-- No rock/wooden tools or armor - all require rare iron-- Cannot convert resources - like stone to iron-- Golems - march out single-file rather than in groups - completely useless endgame - since despite essence cost - do no magic damg"
