,Not Recommended,328080,34725481,Posted: 3 September,all,Leonox,"I've only played traditional or whatever the normal mode is. Overall it's a decent game that seems to tie together a lot of elements from other similar games, making an attempt at covering a lot of aspects from those games that I enjoy.Issues thus far. Game is EA, so obviously there are going to be issues. The dev is super responsive, my problem is that from some of his responses, some changes haven't come even though he commented about them a year ago. For example, if you accidentally dismantle a building, there's no obvious way to stop this. Researching it shows a comment from the dev stating this function is planned for InDev 18, the game is now on InDev 28.This really ties into another issue, it's a combination of the game having a small playerbase and the dev probably being indie, there's no updated wiki to look up the game in its current state. The wiki link on the game's official site gives you a WIP page. Trying to look up information on the game leads to posts that span years, making it unreliable on whether or not it's still relevant.I also have a pretty big issue with the way your buildable area expands. Your walls cut off your ""sphere of influence"" and you can't build beyond your them. This forces you to tear down walls in order to release your ""SOI"" in order to build beyond it. This makes it a huge pain in the♥♥♥♥♥to expand. It's constant leapfrogging your sphere to expand and it gets rather repetitive.As a final note, props to the dev for being super responsive. This however, leads to another con for me. The dev has indicated some game decisions that I don't really agree with.For example, I'm in my second game on traditional, it took me some time figuring out how to get things going in my first attempt so I abandoned it after 20ish minutes to restart. My 2nd and current game started a bit hairy, but now I control like 40% of the map and it's just a slow grind at this point. I realize that I'm playing the easiest mode in probably an easy mapset, my issue is that I don't really feel like doing it all over again because of the time investment to build from the ground up again.I know the dev has made responses as to speeding up the game, my problem is with his responses. The dev has indicated that he wants to add a spell to the game as a temporary buff to your villagers speed instead of just adding a game speed option. My problem with this is that a speed buff is pretty much irrelevant to the issue game speed, they're two entirely different things and the fact that the dev thought this was a response makes me doubt his decision making and the future of the game.The lack of a game speed option is pretty much deterring me from wanting to try any other maps. Sure, it might be harder and the challenge might be a bit more interesting, but there's just too much sitting and waiting for your villagers to get anything done. Especially when you do get strong enough and start having to expand your base.I'm 9.5 hours into the game and pretty much finished with it in my opinion. I got it on sale so I guess I got my money's worth, I'd recommend the game for a quick play, but for the type of game it is, that relies on replayability, I think it still needs a lot of work which might never come, so I can't really recommend it."
