76561198218334892,Recommended,328080,30953288,Posted: 4 April,all,dingo,"I enjoyed the first 30 hours of this game in a binge, struggling to learn the mechanics to stave off hunger or dehydration for my villagers, and defending the town from mobs.  Now surviving several winters, I am impressed with the engine feed/stock dynamics, the balancing a complex system as strategy feels satisfactory and time-pressured.  Losing track of many hours of the day is a sign of good enjoyment for this game.  The particle animations and amiga-like pixel art are also super and pleasing.Gameplay reminds of other games like the original Warcraft, dwarf fortress, command & conquer, castles, and simcity classic. All great titles!At this time, I'm not so sure that the ""late game"" -- cross-pollinating to more difficult territories -- will keep me interested to play much longer, as there isn't any kind of reward in sight. I am hopeful as an early access game that the end-game will become more compelling and rewarding at time of release.  Maybe by introduction of unique map features for each village, or some kind of overall crusading plot. I look forward to development updates and highly recommend this title."
