76561198040767576,Recommended,328080,24918648,"Posted: 14 August, 2016",all,Roboticus,"I rate RPC 722/1000. This game strikes a great balance between city-builder in the Banished-eque style (workers moving resources to construction sites) with an ever-more-challenging flood of zombies that your towers must dispatch. It is much more goal-centric than banished as you have to grow your village fast enough to build and maintain sufficient numbers of towers to defeat the growing horde of enemies. The road system is particularly good because the quality (speed) of the roads has a dramatic affect on worker productivity.The pixel-graphics were actually TOO pixely for me and it was often difficult to tell what the villagers were doing. More interactivity that let the user know what was happening in their world (statistics, graphs, better colored overlays) would have helped. The game needs to scale the difficulty up more from day 21 onwards. Once I passed 21, I could make it to 60 mostly afk.  Finally, the game desperately needs a speed setting (hence the afking) to allow the simulation to run and the difficutly to increase."
