,Recommended,328080,34634257,Posted: 31 August,all,⎛⎝Aarki⎠⎞,"If you like games in the style of Dwarf Fortress, Black&White or Populous, this will be perfect for you.The possibility to directly interact with the world, pick up enemies and throw them into a divine smoothie maker is just one aspect of it. You could also syphon magic energy from your castle's mana generators to conjure rain, keeping your followers' crops from dying in the summer heat, or simply teleport resources around to help with building efforts.Then there's the mouldable landscape that changes as forests are cut down and regrow, mountains are strip-mined away and resurface in massive earthquakes, and disasters like blood moon (it does literally rain blood) that will keep you on your toes. Feeding an ever-increasing population that also requires housing, water and protection from the elements and monsters is another thing on your list, so be prepared for a bit of a learning curve.As for stability and bugs, as long as you stick to the stable version, you should be good. Even if you are more of a bleeding edge indev version addict, you can quickly report bugs and crashes in Discord, and the dev really puts his all into it and gets things fixed in a matter of minutes. Yesterday I reported two minor bugs, today I encountered a CTD, and it's already all hotfixed away.Oh and it also has doggos now, so give it a whirl."
