,Recommended,328080,26053640,"Posted: 15 October, 2016",all,OmniRusted,"Changing my review after a lot of updates, as I promised I would. The dev was nice enough to inform me of incoming updates with problems I had, and the changes are substantial. Defense is still very much a tower defense game, but with a colony survival aspect behind it. If you don't have the proper setup, you will get rolled over by the enemies very quickly.Eventually it seems that the only way to survive is to pull all your leveled-up people (a system that is not explained at all) and go to another area. Realistically you COULD build up until you've conquered an entire map before moving on, but that would take so long it's not really worth it. The game badly, badly needs speed controls.The dev, who is amazingly connected with his community, has said in the future he plans to add ""haste"" or ""slow"" spells, but that doesn't solve the overall problem. Sometimes you don't want to wait around. Sometimes you're okay with the enemy building as fast as you are. Haste and Slow spells will help, yes, but will not solve the problem that eventually the game just gets too grindy.All in all I do recommend this game. Much like Orcs Must Die gave us a third-person tower defense game, this game gives us a colony simulator defense game, and I love that. It's very fun, very challenging, and aside from the few gameplay problems (which the dev will absolutely fix eventually) a gem of a game.Graphics: 2/10. There aren't any. There's also a hell of a lot more particle effects than necessary which tend to clutter the screen.Sound: The music and sounds really help gameplay, and make it a relaxing experience.Story: N/AGameplay: 6/10. It has a lot of room to improve, but is still a hidden gem that you should absolutely check out."
