76561198001841569,Recommended,328080,35348590,Posted: 30 September,all,Caridous,"Very solid city-builder/god-game for sure (don't expect currency/research tree, which isn't a problem fyi)Yes, every game of this genre is compared to and held to the standard of RimWorld, but this is no copycat nor a derivative by any stretch. There is no research tree, and the end game is not about getting off the planet. You're simply a god trying to keep your villagers alive (more tower-defence than RW).Not only does it have a rich diversity of buildings (which you can upgrade to improve efficiency), but has multiple spells for its god-game aspect.For those worried about investing in an ""early-access game"" fear not. Not only is it extremely stable, but it has solid content and a very active and response dev (putting forth a poll at one point to gather a consensus as to what direction to direct his roadmap)This is how modern games should be: solid price, money going to an independent, and a dev who listens. Buy the game, support these kind of initiativesExcited to see how its development continues"
,Recommended,328080,35355526,Posted: 30 September,all,CTRL+FU,"I really enjoy this game. It looks and sounds like it just stepped off the Sega Genesis. It even kinda reminds me of the game Megalomania for that system.This is an addictive little city builder/god game/tower defense game hybrid. You spend the majority of your days city building and at night trying to repel mosters with your guards or defensive structures (the tower defense part.) I don't really find myself doing much godhanding until the map has been built up a bit.My favorite part of the game is the city building and management. The tower defense portion is decently done, but it's not at all what keeps me interested. (I honestly get a little annoyed at nighttime, because repelling the monsters takes time away from what I'd rather be doing.) I like having to balance my logistical needs against my defensive needs. Hmmm... farm, well or spray tower...?If you like city builders or tower defense, this is for you. If you like god games, you'll probably enjoy it as well, even though with me I don't use the god powers much at all, and I'm in year four.A FEW CRITICISMS (please fix/change):If you build a wall diagonally, a lot of times your builders will not build or only partially build the corner wall pieces.When I have one item set to build or upgrade, often builders will mill around with the resource needed to finish it, sometimes dropping it on the ground and walking away.Please fix it so that when something is being built and has all the resources but the building isn't at 100% that the builders stay to finish it, instead of doing one or two construction turns on it then walking away. I've waited five minutes for a builder to finsh a structure that had all of the resources but was still waiting at 96% for them to come back.If walls don't take up a building slot, why should gates? That's just stupid. I HATE having all the walls built up save a big gaping hole for the gate I can't build because I used the builing slot for something else.It would be nice to have a way to make the ""way makers"" auto build paths. Maybe not roads, but at least paths. Often times I completely forget they are even there for an hour at a time, and as such they are just wasted people I could be using on another task.AND PLEASE... When you get the notifications that nomads come, or that someone died or whatever, make it so you can click on the banner (or below in the chatbox) to see where the heck they are. I've lost multiple full groups of nomads because I can't find them to ""grab"" them. It's much too hard to all the time see them when you're all zoomed out looking, and as the game progresses and gets overrun with monsters, losing more people really hurts. I mean, to be fair, if you're a god you should already know where they are, so something that zooms you there makes sense.Otherwise, so far I'm really enjoying it and looking to play more."
