v is constantly adding new stuff. There is always something new to try and explore in this game. Say you get bored of the easy beginning in survival mode. Simply turn it up a notch and go to nightmare mode. Then realize that nightmare mode is REDICULOUSLY hard and make some custom rules. Almost every 2 weeks there is some interesting unstable, and just a month or two after that, depending on how big the update is, you get a complete update with amazing new features. Say you find a new bug, which you probably find a small one or more as it is an early access game, talk to the dev, and you may just find that simply a day or two later, BAM, problem solved. Man, Rayvolution HAS to be my favorite developer. He's constantly working on this game, and to put it lightly, it has paid off."
